<dl id="n10093b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10093b">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10093b"> 93(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> guide <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n10093b"><li>FW 449.11 </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/lexqA.htm#n10093b">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/l39qA.htm#n10093b">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n10093b">MS BL 47482b-53v</ms> </li><li>JJA 57:108 <a name="qA3d" href="../../ff/fdra/qda.htm#qA3d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/q/qa3d.htm#n10093b">Draft: III&sect;2A.3</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[from an ordinance of Louis XI]</font> Le roy veut qu&apos;il y ait un office intitul&eacute;: Conseiller Grand-Maistre des coureurs de France. Pour faire le dict &eacute;tablissement, lui sera baill&eacute; bonne commission <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Tous ceux qui seront envoy&eacute;s avec passeport ou attache du Grand-Maistre de la part du roy payeront pour chaque cheval, y compris celui de <mark>la guide</mark> qui les conduira, 10 sols par quatre lie&uuml;es <font color="green">[It is the King&apos;s will that an office be created entitled &lsquo;Grand-Master Counsellor of the French Runners&rsquo;. For the establishment of the aforesaid, a good commission will be delivered to him [&hellip;]</font> All those sent by the King&apos;s appointment, with a passport from the Grand-master will pay for each horse, including that of the guide who leads them, 10 sous for every four leagues] <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 117-19</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
